<title>USA: Reliable's stock jumps on takeover news.</title>
<headline>Reliable's stock jumps on takeover news.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK</dateline>
<text>
<p>The stock of Reliable Life Insurance Co. leaped more than $48 Thursday, one day after Unitrin Inc. announced a takeover of the life and health insurance company.</p>
<p>Reliable was up $48.50 at $121 on the Nasdaq market, while Unitrin, which is also in the life and health insurance business, was up 37.5 cents at $53.25 on the same exchange.</p>
<p>Under the deal, which was announced late Wednesday, stockholders of Reliable Class A common stock would receive 2.235 shares of Unitrin common stock, or $119 in cash.</p>
<p>Reliable sells life and health insurance in Missouri, Arkansas and Texas.</p>
